  "number": "1.1",
  "title": "Summary",
  "body": " Summary   Included below is a summary of comparisons between the nine University of Louisiana System ( ULS ) schools   Grambling State University ( GSU ),    McNeese State University ( MSU ),    Nicholls State University ( NSU ),    Northwestern State University of Louisiana ( NSULA ),    Southeastern Louisiana University ( SELU ),    Louisiana Tech University ( LTU ),    University of Louisiana at Lafayette ( ULL ),    University of Louisiana at Monroe ( ULM ), and    University of New Orleans ( UNO ).       Institution Type  The following data was gathered in part from the Carnegie Classification of Institutions of Higher Education :   Carnegie Classification            Basic    Graduate Instruction    Enrollment   Math Degrees     ULM    Doctoral\/Professional Universities    Professional-Dominant    High Undergraduate    B.S.      GSU    Master’s Colleges & Universities: Larger Programs    Research Doctoral: Single Program: Education    Very High Undergraduate    B.S.      MSU    Basic: Master's Programs & University: Larger Program    Postbaccalaureate: Comprehensive Programs    High Undergraduate     B.S. , M.S.       NSU    Master's Colleges & Universities: Medium Programs    Postbaccalaureate: Education-Dominant: With Arts & Sciences    Very High Undergraduate     B.S. , M.S.       NSULA    Master's Colleges & Universities: Larger Programs    Postbaccalaureate: Education-Dominant: With Arts & Sciences    Very High Undergraduate    B.S.      SELU    Master's Programs & University: Larger Program    Single Program: Education    Very High Undergraduate     B.S. , M.S.       LTU    High Research Activity    Research Doctoral: Professional-Dominant    High Undergraduate     B.S. , M.S. , Ph.D.       ULL    Very High Research Activity    Research Doctoral: STEM-Dominant    High Undergraduate     B.S. , M.S. , Ph.D.       UNO    High Research Activity    Research Doctoral: Professional-Dominant    High Undergraduate     B.S. , M.S.         Mathematics Credit Hours  The minimum number of credit hours in mathematics required varies by each institution. In order to compare with the concentrations ULM has to offer, the following table provides the number of credit hours in mathematics for four categories   Core  This is the number of credit hours in Mathematics shared by all concentrations that are available at the institution.    Pure  This is the number of credit hours in Mathematics for a degree program in Pure Mathematics. The value N\/A indicates the institution does not provide this concentration.    Act.  This is the number of credit hours in Mathematics for a degree program in Mathematics with a concentration in Actuarial Sciences. The value N\/A indicates the institution does not provide this concentration.    Math.  Ed.  This is the number of credit hours in Mathematics for a degree program in Mathematics with a concentration in Mathematics Education. The value N\/A indicates the institution does not provide this concentration.    Core\/X  This represents the percentage of concentration filled out by core classes, if applicable.      Minimum Required Math Credit Hours by Institution      Core  Pure  Core\/Pure  Act.  Core\/ Act.  Math.  Ed.  Core\/ Math.  Ed.    ULM  16  31  51.61%  31  51.61%  30  53.33%    GSU  18  N\/A   30  60.00%  N\/A     MSU  29  47  61.70%  N\/A   41  70.73%    NSU  28  43  65.12%  N\/A   31  90.32%    NSULA  30  45  66.67%  45  66.67%  N\/A     SELU  25  43  58.14%  43  58.14%  43  58.14%    LTU  50  50  100%  N\/A   N\/A     ULL  42  42  100%  N\/A   N\/A     UNO  30  45  66.67%  48  62.50%  N\/A     Avg.  29.78  43.25  71.24%  39.4  59.78%  36.25  68.13%       Required Courses  The core curriculum is not standard across ULS institutions. The table below indicates whether the core curriculum for a given institution includes or does not include the following common courses:   LA  This is a course on Linear Algebra similar to MATH 2002 Applied Linear Algebra.    FM  This is a course that introduces the basics of logic and proof, similar to MATH 2040 Foundations of Mathematics    DE  This is a course on Ordinary Differential Equations, similar to MATH 3001 Differential Equations.    MS  This is a course similar to MATH 3003 Mathematical Statistics.    RA  This is a course on Advanced Calculus\/Introductory Real Analysis similar to MATH 3080 Real Analysis.    MA  This is a course on Modern\/Abstract Algebra, similar to MATH 3086 Modern Algebra.      Course Requirements (All Concentrations) by Institution     ULM  GSU  MSU  NSU  NSULA  SELU  LTU  ULL  UNO  Total    LA  Y  Y  Y  Y  Y  Y  Y  Y  Y  9    FM  Y  N  Y  Y  Y  Y  Y  Y  Y  8    DE  N  Y  Y  Y  N  N  Y  Y  N  5    MS  Y  Y  N  Y  N  Y  N  N  N  4    RA  N  N  N  N  N  N  Y  N  Y  1    MA  N  N  Y  Y  Y  Y  Y  N  Y  6      "
