  "body": " University of New Orleans   The Carnegie Classification of Institutions of Higher Education classification for the University of New Orleans   Basic: Doctoral Universities: High Research Activity    Graduate Instruction: Research Doctoral: Professional-Dominant    Enrollment: High Undergraduate     The department offers a Bachelor of Science in Mathematics , an Actuarial Sciences Concentration , and a Master of Science in Mathematics     Core Courses  All concentrations require the following 30 credit hours of Mathematics courses:   MATH 2114 - Calculus I (4 hours)    MATH 2124 - Calculus II (4 Hours)    MATH 2134 - Calculus III (4 hours)    MATH 3511 - Introduction to Linear Algebra (3 hours)    MATH 3512 - Introduction to Abstract Algebra (3 hours)    MATH 3721 - Introduction to Discrete Structures (3 hours)    Note: This seems to be a course on introduction to proofs, rather than a course on discrete mathematics ( graph theory, combinatorics, ).       MATH 3900 - Undergraduate Oral Examination (0 hours)    MATH 4101 - Advanced Calculus (3 hours)    MATH 3000+ (6 hours)       Mathematics Concentration  In addition to the core courses, the Mathematics Concentration requires the following 15 credit hours of Mathematics courses:   One of   MATH 2221 - Elementary Differential Equations (3 hours)    MATH 2314 - Elementary Statistical Methods (3 hours)       MATH 4511 - Linear Algebra (3 hours)    MATH 4000+ (9 hours)       Actuarial Sciences Concentration  In addition to the core courses, the Actuarial Sciences Concentration requires the following 18 credits hours of Mathematics courses:   MATH 2221 - Elementary Differential Equations (3 hours)    MATH 2314 - Elementary Statistical Methods (3 hours)    MATH 4311 - Introduction to Mathematical Statistics (3 hours)    MATH 4801 - Actuarial Probability I (3 hours)    MATH 4802 - Actuarial Probability II (3 hours)    MATH 4803 - Financial Math I (3 hours)      "
